article.headline: Radford 80, Charleston Southern 71
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Artsiom Parakhouski scored 29 points and Radford defeated Charleston Southern 80-71 on Monday night. Joey Lynch-Flohr and Amir Johnson added 16 points each for the Highlanders (15-10, 12-2 Big South Conference). Johnson was a perfect 6-for-6 from the free-throw line and Parakhouski was 11 of 16 from the field. Radford led by as many as 14 points, 61-47, with 9:22 to play on a free throw by Phillip Martin. The Highlanders shot 50 percent from the field (26 of 52) compared to 43.5 percent (27 of 62) by the Buccaneers (7-12, 2-11). Omar Carter led Charleston Southern with 18 points and 12 rebounds. Jamarco Warren added 16 points and Giedrius Knysas chipped in 14 for the Buccaneers. The Highlanders outrebounded Charleston Southern 35-30, as Parakhouski led the way with eight.
